-- HSBC's sale of Uruguay banking business falls through
-- By Karen Rebelo in Bangalore
-- Mon Mar 31, 2014 10:14AM EDT
-- None



March 31 (Reuters) - HSBC Holdings Plc <HSBA.L> said an agreement to sell its banking business in Uruguay to Banco GNB Sudameris had ended.

HSBC, Europe's biggest bank by market capitalisation, did not give a reason for the agreement falling through, but said on Monday that it was exploring alternative options for a sale of the business. [ID:nRSe5916Da] HSBC struck a deal in 2012 to sell its operations in Colombia, Uruguay, Peru and Paraguay for $400 million to Banco GNB Sudameris [GNBSU.UL].